The Purcell enhanced emitter has furthermore a cavity-enhanced quantum yield ηon that can be significantly larger compared to the reference system, since the Purcell enhanced radiative rate catches up with all NR losses in the system. Ultimately ηon cannot reach exactly unity in plasmonic systems since the metal loss cannot be entirely avoided. At best, for high enough Purcell factors γR≫γNR\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
